GERMANY BLACK FRIDAY SOLIDARITY PROTEST
Black Friday solidarity protest for Polish women in Berlin
People take part in a 'Black Friday' protest to support a Polish Women's nationwide strike against the tightening of the abortion law in Poland, in Berlin, Germany, 23 March 2018. The Polish Parliament's Justice and Human Rights Committe on 19 March approved a civic project on ban of abortion law in Poland. The project assumes the abolition of the possibility of termination of pregnancy due to severe and irreversible defects of the fetus. Polish National Women Strike movemnet announced country wide protests called 'Black Friday' against the project on 23 March 2018. EPA/OMER MESSINGER
 